## What the composite metric means

The `${rubric_name}_composite` metric is a single float in `[0, 1]` (higher is
better) computed by `scorer.py` as the weighted arithmetic mean of the rubric
criteria, multiplied by hard-gate pass/fail indicators. It is always in `[0, 1]`
regardless of the underlying task semantics — `/auto researcher`'s
`metric_direction: higher` is unambiguous.

When the agent improves the composite by more than `min_delta`, `/auto researcher`
keeps the change. When the composite drops by more than `min_delta`, the change
is reverted. When a hard gate fails, `scorer.py` exits with non-zero status —
`/auto researcher` records this as a `crashed` row in `EXPERIMENT_LOG.md` with
the gate's reason visible in the diagnostic, **not** as a silent low score.

